routeFacts.name: Tees Valley Line
routeFacts.description: The Tees Valley Line is a route DLC for Train Sim World, featuring the Tees Valley Line between Darlington and Saltburn, a length of 27 miles. The route is set in 1989 during the sectorisation of British Rail and featured with the route are the BR Class 08, Class 37, and both 2-car and 3-car Class 101.
routeInfo:
The route covers the Tees Valley Line in the North East of England from Darlington to Saltburn via Middlesbrough and Redcar.
Set in 1989, the route is used by both passenger and freight services which served the many industries located along the route.
